  "doc_id": "889",
  "text": "A Nikon PCM2000 laser scanning confocal microscope was used. PSII chlorophyll fluorescence was visualized with excitation at 457 nm and emission at >665 nm defined by a Schott RG665 red glass filter . Red light pretreatments were applied by scanning the confocal spot from a 633-nm HeNe laser over the sample. Comparable pretreatments with blue and green light were applied using the 457-nm line of an argon laser and a 543-nm green HeNe laser. FRAP measurements were performed as described previously . Data analysis was as described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , except that the diffusion equation included an additional term to allow for the possibility of an immobile fraction.",
